ll same as ls -l

ls -l | more - to scroll page by page
ls =l | tail -1 - to show the last file or directory

ls -ltr

mkdir folder - makes a folder
rm filename - removes file
mv filename - renames

3 types of help commands:
whatis - command - example - whatis chmod
--help - command - example - chmod --help
man - command - example - man chmod

introduction to text editor - vi
i - insert
esc - escape
r - replace
d - delete
:q! - quit without saving
:wq! - quit and save

USER ACCOUNT MANAGEMENT:
commands:
useradd
groupadd
userdel
groupdel

history - shows history of your previous commands
when your history shows up, use "!18" to select it

wc - word count
wc /etc/passwd

ctrl + R - search through your history
ctrl + A - goes to beginning of terminal
ctrl + E - goes to end of terminal line
ctrl + left or right arrow - will allow you to skip words in your terminal
ctrl + k - deletes from cursor to end
ctrl + u - deletes from curso to the beginning

to clear screen:
clear or ctrl + l
